Two
species of commercial value in the genus 

Farfantepenaeus
Burukovsky, 1997

known as “pink shrimp” are predominant in coastal areas of the 
southwestern Atlantic Ocean
: 

Farfantepenaeus brasiliensis
(Latreille, 1817)

and 

Farfantepenaeus paulensis
(Pérez Farfante, 1967)

